From 46d941293e5ef81b94a8130dfe7afb042480cbd1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Micay <danielmicay@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 15 May 2017 23:45:34 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 068/104] ata: avoid null pointer dereference on bug

Extracted from PaX.

[nicolas.bouchinet@ssi.gouv.fr: BUG_ON NULL ptr deref removed in 5bb52d926598a0]
Signed-off-by: Nicolas Bouchinet <nicolas.bouchinet@ssi.gouv.fr>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Micay <danielmicay@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/ata/libata-core.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/ata/libata-core.c b/drivers/ata/libata-core.c
index 4fb8990d22d5..c5f63427ede7 100644
--- a/drivers/ata/libata-core.c
+++ b/drivers/ata/libata-core.c
@@ -4849,6 +4849,7 @@ void __ata_qc_complete(struct ata_queued_cmd *qc)
 	struct ata_port *ap;
 	struct ata_link *link;
 
+	BUG_ON(qc == NULL); /* ata_qc_from_tag _might_ return NULL */
 	if (WARN_ON_ONCE(!(qc->flags & ATA_QCFLAG_ACTIVE)))
 		return;
 
